race.comment: STAR TERRITORY (5) drifted well back when resuming last start before winding up strongly to just miss when third over 1203m at Kyneton. Draws marginally better this time, so might settle a shade closer and with extra fitness deserves to be considered the testing material. SHAME ON SUE (10) is usually thereabouts but finds it hard to win, with only one victory from 13 starts. Again tasted defeat last start when seventh over 1100m at Colac, beaten 3 lengths, but finds an easier assignment and can get the job done. BEFORE THE WAR (2) won't be wanting for fitness now and is back from a couple of respectable runs in 62 grade. MAGIC LEPRECHAUN (3) appreciated the step up to 1203m last start, when beat home STAR TERRITORY, so he can't be dismissed.
